139
00:07:32,441 --> 00:07:34,241
Cover up the small things.

140
00:07:34,681 --> 00:07:35,811
If we cook this right,

141
00:07:36,451 --> 00:07:39,021
no one will be able to point out anything specific.

142
00:07:39,022 --> 00:07:41,522
It's like they're talking in codes.

143
00:07:42,292 --> 00:07:44,191
They're working so hard to build something...

144
00:07:44,592 --> 00:07:45,792
that will be torn down.

145
00:07:49,332 --> 00:07:50,991
Someone will trip over this.

146
00:07:51,391 --> 00:07:53,861
Move this pallet, Mr. Kim.

147
00:07:53,862 --> 00:07:55,431
- Okay. - Mr. Jang.

148
00:07:58,371 --> 00:07:59,741
There were accountants here.

149
00:08:00,241 --> 00:08:01,772
They come every quarter.

150
00:08:02,342 --> 00:08:04,440
But this time, they were saying...

151
00:08:04,441 --> 00:08:05,482
Look.

152
00:08:06,042 --> 00:08:08,311
Are you studying to become a police officer like you wanted to?

153
00:08:09,082 --> 00:08:11,250
If you go around fighting all the time,

154
00:08:11,251 --> 00:08:13,921
you'll die alone or of fatigue.

155
00:08:13,922 --> 00:08:15,690
(Steel storage yard)

156
00:08:15,691 --> 00:08:18,022
And you should wear a hard hat.

157
00:08:20,092 --> 00:08:21,391
Mr. Jang.

158
00:08:26,062 --> 00:08:28,501
The cold air is getting in and the residents...

159
00:08:28,901 --> 00:08:30,572
I haven't seen Yeo Jin today.

160
00:08:31,072 --> 00:08:33,572
I didn't, either.

161
00:08:33,901 --> 00:08:36,141
She's so busy...

162
00:08:36,442 --> 00:08:38,380
- preparing for the police exam. - Right.

163
00:08:38,381 --> 00:08:40,311
Haebit Construction, which had been known...

164
00:08:40,312 --> 00:08:42,250
