Not only that, but I'd also eat with him...

542
00:34:40,702 --> 00:34:42,802
- and go to the sauna with him. - Eat this.

543
00:34:43,072 --> 00:34:44,341
Thank you.

544
00:34:44,342 --> 00:34:46,342
You should have asked me first...

545
00:34:51,351 --> 00:34:52,612
Hello.

546
00:35:05,262 --> 00:35:07,600
Certainly, all public announcements published...

547
00:35:07,601 --> 00:35:09,500
by accounting firms are important.

548
00:35:09,501 --> 00:35:12,802
However, the most important one is the audit report.

549
00:35:13,541 --> 00:35:16,710
Our audit reports influence not only the company...

550
00:35:16,711 --> 00:35:18,841
but also the shareholders.

551
00:35:18,842 --> 00:35:22,381
More than anything else, they require extra care.

552
00:35:30,992 --> 00:35:34,592
Profits and losses look good, but they don't have enough cash flow.

553
00:35:39,762 --> 00:35:41,032
You scum.

554
00:35:41,601 --> 00:35:43,671
Stand straight!

555
00:35:44,972 --> 00:35:48,471
How dare you handle it like that?

556
00:35:48,472 --> 00:35:49,841
Dad, I can explain...

557
00:35:49,842 --> 00:35:52,871
As the major shareholder, even if Bo Sung tries...

558
00:35:52,872 --> 00:35:55,281
to shove money into it,

559
00:35:55,282 --> 00:35:57,751
you should have been firm and stopped him.

560
00:35:58,182 --> 00:36:02,421
Are you sure that you covered up the mess he created in the books?

561
00:36:04,691 --> 00:36:06,891
Yes, I did as you told me.

562
00:36:06,892 --> 00:36:11,092
If it gets revealed, you will be responsible for it all, got it?

563
00:36:11,892 --> 00:36:13,191
Darn it.

564
00:36:17,731 --> 00:36:19,001
Goodness.

565
00:36:23,372 --> 00:36:27,012
I am sure...

566
00:36:27,541 --> 00:36:31,682
that Bo Sung's intention was good.

567
00:36:32,311 --> 00:36:35,350
After having a meeting with China, when an article...

568
00:36:35,351 --> 00:36:38,721
about my duty-free business was published, the stock price soared.

569
00:36:38,722 --> 00:36:40,092
You punk!

570
00:36:40,722 --> 00:36:43,060
That place where you wanted to open up your business,

571
00:36:43,061 --> 00:36:44,661
the branch office reassessment went haywire,

572
00:36:44,662 --> 00:36:46,231
so they're about to go bankrupt.

573
00:36:46,702 --> 00:36:49,601
If you want to start something, you should know the details.

574
00:36:49,932 --> 00:36:51,572
There's no authenticity in your lies.

575
00:36:52,372 --> 00:36:55,371
You're amazing. Now, you look like a real chairman.

576
00:36:55,372 --> 00:36:57,072
Why you...

577
00:36:57,941 --> 00:37:01,210
The prosecutors could be after us for embezzlement and malfeasance.

578
00:37:01,211 --> 00:37:03,242
You'd better come to your senses.

579
00:37:06,412 --> 00:37:08,251
We are here for you...

580
00:37:11,722 --> 00:37:14,021
to prevent such a thing.

581
00:37:16,461 --> 00:37:19,091
Generally, embezzlement and malfeasance occur...

582
00:37:19,092 --> 00:37:21,661
when shareholders lose their money.

583
00:37:21,662 --> 00:37:24,431
In other words, if we make them gain money instead,

584
00:37:24,432 --> 00:37:25,972
the problem will disappear right away.

585
00:37:26,671 --> 00:37:29,142
What if Sangha Group takes over People's Entertainment?

586
00:37:29,202 --> 00:37:32,142
Then the problem will be yours.

587
00:37:32,742 --> 00:37:36,142
Sangha Group would be taking over a company at the risk of delisting.

588
00:37:36,311 --> 00:37:38,580
What else can I do?

589
00:37:38,581 --> 00:37:40,452
Should I let my son get arrested?

590
00:37:40,682 --> 00:37:42,951
First, do everything you can so that People's Entertainment...

591
00:37:42,952 --> 00:37:46,092
gets an unqualified opinion...

592
00:37:47,722 --> 00:37:49,162
from this year's audit.

593
00:37:49,722 --> 00:37:54,001
Once you stabilize the company's financials with recapitalization,

594
00:37:54,432 --> 00:37:57,131
you may take over the company.

595
00:37:57,631 --> 00:37:59,701
As long as you follow this order and do it on time,

596
00:37:59,702 --> 00:38:02,472
both you and your son will be safe.

597
00:38:03,401 --> 00:38:07,881
What if People's Entertainment doesn't get an unqualified opinion?

598
00:38:07,941 --> 00:38:09,112
It will be a fiasco.

599
00:38:09,441 --> 00:38:14,182
We will take care of it...

600
00:38:14,682 --> 00:38:16,351
with the accounting firm.

601
00:38:18,851 --> 00:38:23,362
Gosh, I knew that you would handle it.

602
00:38:23,791 --> 00:38:27,662
Three years ago, when they conducted a surprise slush fund investigation,

603
00:38:27,961 --> 00:38:31,331
what he pulled off was unbelievable.

604
00:38:35,072 --> 00:38:36,372
Gosh.

605
00:38:40,182 --> 00:38:42,080
Like father, like son,

606
00:38:42,081 --> 00:38:44,581
they aren't much different from one another.

607
00:38:45,552 --> 00:38:47,621
It's unfortunate for Sangha Group,

608
00:38:47,622 --> 00:38:49,881
but it's good news for our accounting firm.

609
00:38:50,081 --> 00:38:52,051
As a result, the pitch was a piece of cake.

610
00:38:52,052 --> 00:38:53,350
(Pitch: a presentation of services to clients to get a project)

611
00:38:53,351 --> 00:38:54,361
That is true.

612
00:38:54,362 --> 00:38:56,831
We got a mergers and acquisitions case without intending to.

613
00:39:02,461 --> 00:39:04,801
An incompetent CEO is...

614
00:39:04,802 --> 00:39:07,242
the most competent client for an accounting firm.

615
00:39:45,742 --> 00:39:47,981
They definitely deserve an unqualified opinion.

616
00:39:48,512 --> 00:39:51,850
There's no serious error for a disclaimer of opinion.

617
00:39:51,851 --> 00:39:54,421
If we disclaim our opinion, and they get delisted,

618
00:39:54,481 --> 00:39:57,592
the shareholders will protest and sue us.

619
00:39:57,651 --> 00:39:59,850
The consequences will be serious.

620
00:39:59,851 --> 00:40:02,991
If we take the easy way out to satisfy everyone...

621
00:40:02,992 --> 00:40:05,331
when they deserve a disclaimer of opinion,

622
00:40:05,592 --> 00:40:07,801
the worst consequence would be when a problem rises.

623
00:40:07,802 --> 00:40:09,661
If we give an unqualified opinion, and the firm gets in trouble,

624
00:40:09,662 --> 00:40:10,770
how will you handle that?

625
00:40:10,771 --> 00:40:13,701
Aren't you going overboard with something that hasn't happened?

626
00:40:13,702 --> 00:40:16,541
Besides, who wants a disclaimer of opinion?

627
00:40:16,941 --> 00:40:18,940
Neither People's Entertainment, their shareholders,

628
00:40:18,941 --> 00:40:21,881
their lending banks, nor creditors want that.

629
00:40:22,012 --> 00:40:24,210
This disclaimer of opinion is for whom?

630
00:40:24,211 --> 00:40:27,721
Aren't public accountants supposed to work for the public?

631
00:40:27,722 --> 00:40:29,350
If something looks doubtful,

632
00:40:29,351 --> 00:40:32,191
isn't it only right to give them a disclaimer of opinion?

633
00:40:34,222 --> 00:40:35,921
It requires prudence.

634
00:40:36,521 --> 00:40:39,032
An accounting firm's disclaimer of opinion can result...

635
00:40:39,061 --> 00:40:41,401
in delisting of the company.

636
00:40:41,901 --> 00:40:46,831
In other words, the fate of everyone with interest in the company...

637
00:40:47,072 --> 00:40:50,101
depends on the accounting firm's decision.

638
00:40:52,912 --> 00:40:54,711
Haebit Construction is now bankrupt.

639
00:40:55,512 --> 00:40:56,612
Mr. Jang?

640
00:40:56,912 --> 00:40:58,881
Mr. Jang.

641
00:41:00,151 --> 00:41:02,052
Mr. Jang!

642
00:41:11,932 --> 00:41:15,561
That will be all for today.

643
00:41:15,961 --> 00:41:17,131
Thank you for listening.

644
00:41:17,231 --> 00:41:18,572
- Thank you. - Thank you.

645
00:41:32,481 --> 00:41:33,751
He will think it over,

646
00:41:34,182 --> 00:41:37,392
but Mr. Kang is unlikely to give a disclaimer of opinion.

647
00:41:37,751 --> 00:41:39,691
It may be called a disclaimer of opinion,

648
00:41:40,592 --> 00:41:42,722
but it's the same as a death sentence.

649
00:41:45,191 --> 00:41:48,501
He has known CEO Koo for several years.

650
00:41:49,702 --> 00:41:51,171
It won't be easy to betray him.

651
00:41:51,572 --> 00:41:53,001
It will not be easy.

652
00:41:53,802 --> 00:41:56,901
However, it must be done.

653
00:41:58,972 --> 00:42:01,282
I will take care of it without causing problems.

654
00:42:07,182 --> 00:42:08,282
I'll call you back.

655
00:42:13,052 --> 00:42:14,162
You must be busy.

656
00:42:15,322 --> 00:42:17,092
Just like any other busy season.

657
00:42:19,532 --> 00:42:21,302
You once said...

658
00:42:21,932 --> 00:42:24,401
that doing the best may not be for the best.

659
00:42:25,472 --> 00:42:26,831
Do you remember?

660
00:42:28,472 --> 00:42:29,901
When I was a new staff member,

661
00:42:30,711 --> 00:42:33,211
I could have reviewed a sample,

662
00:42:33,441 --> 00:42:36,142
but I insisted on reviewing the entire account.

663
00:42:36,242 --> 00:42:39,081
I almost stopped you from finishing the report.

664
00:42:39,811 --> 00:42:41,881
It's what you told me back then.

665
00:42:43,151 --> 00:42:44,921
He may be doing his best,

666
00:42:45,492 --> 00:42:47,892
but it may not be the best for everyone.

667
00:42:49,822 --> 00:42:52,231
It came to my mind today all of a sudden.

668
00:42:53,561 --> 00:42:56,731
There was an obvious answer that everyone agreed with,

669
00:42:57,231 --> 00:42:59,671
but why did I insist on it...

670
00:43:00,131 --> 00:43:02,072
thinking that it was my conviction?

671
00:43:07,211 --> 00:43:09,581
Are you saying there's something...

672
00:43:10,282 --> 00:43:11,512
I'm not allowed to try my best?

673
00:43:12,981 --> 00:43:15,581
It seemed like you had something to tell me...

674
00:43:15,822 --> 00:43:17,492
by bringing up past stories you don't even like.

675
00:43:20,521 --> 00:43:22,221
I get that you want to say...

676
00:43:22,222 --> 00:43:25,532
the answer people say is okay is also the best for everyone.

677
00:43:26,162 --> 00:43:28,001
But who's included in the "people" in this case?

678
00:43:29,302 --> 00:43:30,702
And who is "everyone?"

679
00:44:15,081 --> 00:44:16,782
The documents I mentioned aren't here.

680
00:44:17,811 --> 00:44:20,750
I asked you about them days ago. Why are they still not here?

681
00:44:20,751 --> 00:44:22,981
I'm not able to do any work because of this.

682
00:44:23,151 --> 00:44:24,651
Hurry up and bring it to me now.

683
00:44:25,322 --> 00:44:29,322
I mentioned this to you ages ago. How come they're still not here?

684
00:44:29,461 --> 00:44:30,762
Bring them over right now.

685
00:44:33,731 --> 00:44:35,032
Senior Associate Park.

686
00:44:35,802 --> 00:44:38,271
- What is it? - Is there anything I can help with?

687
00:44:39,501 --> 00:44:41,342
I'm fine. Just go do your job.

688
00:44:41,572 --> 00:44:42,601
My job.

689
00:44:43,242 --> 00:44:45,912
I have nothing to do. That's why I'm asking for work.

690
00:44:49,311 --> 00:44:51,251
I'm currently not involved in any projects,

691
00:44:51,581 --> 00:44:54,182
so I was thinking I'd help with whatever you're doing.

692
00:44:55,351 --> 00:44:56,381
It's Teacher.

693
00:44:57,421 --> 00:44:59,091
- Pardon? - Regardless of rank,

694
00:44:59,092 --> 00:45:02,461
that's the official term that accountants call each other here.

695
00:45:02,992 --> 00:45:05,231
Oh, right. Teacher.

696
00:45:07,862 --> 00:45:10,162
Teacher Jang Ho Woo. You don't have any work?

697
00:45:11,432 --> 00:45:12,471
That's right.

698
00:45:12,472 --> 00:45:14,072
Have you ever seen results without cause?

699
00:45:14,372 --> 00:45:16,670
Haven't you thought that there must be a reason...

700
00:45:16,671 --> 00:45:18,411
why no one needs you on their team?

701
00:45:18,412 --> 00:45:19,670
What could that reason be?

702
00:45:19,671 --> 00:45:22,081
I couldn't figure it out, no matter how much I tried, Teacher.

703
00:45:22,211 --> 00:45:23,512
You must've misunderstood me.

704
00:45:24,211 --> 00:45:25,611
We may call each other Teacher here,

705
00:45:25,612 --> 00:45:27,581
but I didn't mean I'd teach you anything.

706
00:45:30,151 --> 00:45:31,622
Is it because I didn't go to college?

707
00:45:32,251 --> 00:45:34,560
I may not have a college degree, but I passed the accountant exam.

708
00:45:34,561 --> 00:45:36,892
And I went through the proper process to join this firm.

709
00:45:37,061 --> 00:45:39,630
Why is it suddenly a problem that I didn't go to college?

710
00:45:39,631 --> 00:45:40,831
Do you think that's the reason?

711
00:45:41,731 --> 00:45:44,101
If you think that's it, then you must be right.

712
00:45:48,072 --> 00:45:49,441
Do you still have more to say?

713
00:45:49,671 --> 00:45:51,472
I don't have anything to say, but I do have a lot to do.

714
00:46:09,892 --> 00:46:11,591
Send it to me for review once you're done.

715
00:46:11,592 --> 00:46:12,631
Yes, sir.

716
00:46:51,631 --> 00:46:53,631
What will you do if you meet him looking like this?

717
00:47:11,021 --> 00:47:14,092
Wasn't there anyone who told you that you shouldn't come up here?

718
00:47:37,211 --> 00:47:39,012
Didn't you run away from the office?

719
00:47:40,052 --> 00:47:41,521
It seems like you went to the restroom.

720
00:47:48,162 --> 00:47:49,461
Unfortunately,

721
00:47:51,892 --> 00:47:53,762
your anger doesn't have any power to it.

722
00:47:57,372 --> 00:47:59,500
Do you really believe people won't work with you...

723
00:47:59,501 --> 00:48:01,041
and bully you because you didn't go to college?

724
00:48:01,771 --> 00:48:03,170
"We don't want an accountant without a college diploma..."

725
00:48:03,171 --> 00:48:04,572
"and muddying the waters."

726
00:48:05,612 --> 00:48:07,242
- Isn't that it? - You're wrong.

727
00:48:08,012 --> 00:48:09,380
Whether you only went to high school or middle school,

728
00:48:09,381 --> 00:48:10,711
none of the accountants here...

729
00:48:11,311 --> 00:48:12,552
care at all.

730
00:48:13,282 --> 00:48:16,421
Who cares when your paycheck isn't coming out of my pocket?

731
00:48:17,751 --> 00:48:19,750
- Then why... - Regardless of your education,

732
00:48:19,751 --> 00:48:22,060
you joined my team...

733
00:48:22,061 --> 00:48:23,921
and you're affecting my income?

734
00:48:24,592 --> 00:48:25,791
Now, that's a different story.

735
00:48:27,432 --> 00:48:28,600
Is this about money?

736
00:48:28,601 --> 00:48:30,162
This is about whether you can prove...

737
00:48:30,702 --> 00:48:33,071
that you can pull your own weight...

738
00:48:33,072 --> 00:48:34,441
as a team member.

739
00:48:36,171 --> 00:48:37,202
Prove it?

740
00:48:38,142 --> 00:48:39,342
Time Report.

741
00:48:40,171 --> 00:48:41,981
You would've heard of it during the New Staff Orientation.

742
00:48:43,012 --> 00:48:45,150
It's a Profitability Evaluation to go over...

743
00:48:45,151 --> 00:48:48,181
how many accountants were on this case, spent how much time,

744
00:48:48,182 --> 00:48:49,421
and made how much money in profit.

745
00:48:52,291 --> 00:48:53,822
(Notice, Time Code Approval)

746
00:48:58,191 --> 00:48:59,631
How many did we get assigned?

747
00:48:59,892 --> 00:49:00,901
Six.

748
00:49:01,202 --> 00:49:03,532
Oh, with six staff, we should be able to work with ease.

749
00:49:04,831 --> 00:49:06,501
Wait, why don't you look relieved?

750
00:49:07,601 --> 00:49:10,071
We're working with six people. I'm worried we might spend...

751
00:49:10,072 --> 00:49:11,441
all that time and not make enough profit.

752
00:49:11,671 --> 00:49:13,972
It's better to take five guys who are trustworthy.

753
00:49:14,481 --> 00:49:16,742
It might be more physically tiring, but we'd feel a lot more at ease.

754
00:49:16,941 --> 00:49:19,350
You're right. If one of them messes up,

755
00:49:19,351 --> 00:49:21,722
the whole team has to pay the price.

756
00:49:22,452 --> 00:49:24,190
One time, a new staff did...

757
00:49:24,191 --> 00:49:26,392
such a thorough job of messing things up.

758
00:49:26,822 --> 00:49:29,892
He practically dug a grave to bury the entire team in.

759
00:49:30,162 --> 00:49:32,791
The size of the grave was like a royal tomb.

760
00:49:33,291 --> 00:49:37,000
This could mean getting passed over for raises, bonuses, and promotions,

761
00:49:37,001 --> 00:49:40,372
and you might end up with an incapable teammate for a whole year.

762
00:49:40,631 --> 00:49:42,441
Of course, you can't make such decisions lightly.

763
00:49:43,372 --> 00:49:44,811
But what? School relations and educational background?

764
00:49:45,572 --> 00:49:46,642
Do you think it's that easy?

765
00:49:46,941 --> 00:49:49,381
If it were you, would it be that simple?

766
00:49:49,541 --> 00:49:51,682
Then why don't you just say it outright like,

767
00:49:52,052 --> 00:49:53,781
"This is this, and that's that?"

768
00:49:53,782 --> 00:49:55,322
This place isn't a school.

769
00:49:55,921 --> 00:49:57,621
You might have a duty to learn,

770
00:49:57,622 --> 00:49:59,622
but we don't have a duty to teach you.

771
00:50:00,592 --> 00:50:03,091
And even if someone teaches you, it's for one's own benefit.

772
00:50:03,092 --> 00:50:04,461
It's not for your sake.

773
00:50:05,092 --> 00:50:07,831
Besides, risk analyses, valuations, and expected earnings...

774
00:50:09,432 --> 00:50:11,601
Shouldn't you be familiar with these terms if you're an accountant?

775
00:50:12,932 --> 00:50:15,071
You are a clear risk that you didn't go to college,

776
00:50:15,072 --> 00:50:16,641
your capability is unknown,

777
00:50:16,642 --> 00:50:18,211
and your teamwork hasn't been experienced by anyone before.

778
00:50:18,512 --> 00:50:20,412
Naturally, the expected earnings become unclear.

779
00:50:21,282 --> 00:50:22,580
You would've figured it out soon...

780
00:50:22,581 --> 00:50:24,251
if you had thought about it like an accountant.

781
00:50:25,452 --> 00:50:26,811
Did you not see it because you were anxious?

782
00:50:30,081 --> 00:50:31,520
Why were you in such a rush to get here...

783
00:50:31,521 --> 00:50:32,952
that you even skipped college?

784
00:50:33,822 --> 00:50:35,791
What on earth do you want to do here?

785
00:50:40,092 --> 00:50:41,101
Forget it.

786
00:50:41,202 --> 00:50:43,331
I'm not curious. I don't need to know.

787
00:50:47,702 --> 00:50:49,441
Go downstairs unless you're going to smoke.

788
00:50:51,872 --> 00:50:53,572
Even if I were in charge,

789
00:50:54,881 --> 00:50:56,311
I wouldn't choose you to be on my team.

790
00:51:36,782 --> 00:51:37,952
Hello?

791
00:51:38,521 --> 00:51:39,791
There you go.

792
00:51:40,092 --> 00:51:41,092
What's this?

793
00:51:41,093 --> 00:51:44,291
It's my special kimchi jjigae.

794
00:51:44,932 --> 00:51:46,290
Shall we try it?

795
00:51:46,291 --> 00:51:49,362
I even bought meat to cook this kimchi jjigae for you guys.

796
00:51:52,731 --> 00:51:53,972
Okay. Let's drink.

797
00:52:02,682 --> 00:52:04,141
How is it? Isn't it good?

798
00:52:04,142 --> 00:52:05,580
- It's salty. - I want a refund.

799
00:52:05,581 --> 00:52:07,411
- This is salty? - Add some more water.

800
00:52:07,412 --> 00:52:08,850
If this is salty, you guys are...

801
00:52:08,851 --> 00:52:10,351
- It's salty. - This is salty?

802
00:52:14,492 --> 00:52:15,762
The liquor tastes sweet today.

803
00:52:16,262 --> 00:52:17,631
My life is so bitter.

804
00:52:17,731 --> 00:52:20,162
Gosh, whether it's a police officer on probationary employment...

805
00:52:20,662 --> 00:52:22,061
or an accountant in training...

806
00:52:23,101 --> 00:52:25,331
Do you have to put it that way?

807
00:52:25,831 --> 00:52:28,702
There are only the best of the best at an accounting firm.

808
00:52:29,671 --> 00:52:32,512
And I'm just trying to find a space among them.

809
00:52:34,112 --> 00:52:36,182
That's my job every single day.

810
00:52:36,782 --> 00:52:37,782
Why?

811
00:52:39,381 --> 00:52:40,681
I only have a high school diploma.

812
00:52:40,682 --> 00:52:43,622
Sure. I know how that feels.

813
00:52:44,251 --> 00:52:46,750
No matter how I look at it, Ho Woo should've gone...

814
00:52:46,751 --> 00:52:49,190
to college before becoming an accountant.

815
00:52:49,191 --> 00:52:50,191
Still.

816
00:52:50,521 --> 00:52:52,891
It's better than having to deal with drunks for the past few months.

817
00:52:52,892 --> 00:52:55,000
And it's better than having loans piled up,

818
00:52:55,001 --> 00:52:57,702
but not having customers, making me work part-time during the day.

819
00:52:58,601 --> 00:53:02,342
Besides, you have a friend like me by your side.

820
00:53:02,941 --> 00:53:03,972
Who are you?

821
00:53:04,142 --> 00:53:05,742
Hey. You tell me.

822
00:53:06,072 --> 00:53:08,612
When life is at its worst and you feel so down,

823
00:53:08,842 --> 00:53:11,211
who do you think of?

824
00:53:13,851 --> 00:53:14,921
I think of 911 responders.

825
00:53:16,682 --> 00:53:18,651
Right, 911.

826
00:53:19,052 --> 00:53:20,191
It's not you.

827
00:53:20,791 --> 00:53:22,722
Seriously, 911... Hey, come here.

828
00:53:25,331 --> 00:53:27,032
- You should sleep. - Okay.

829
00:54:02,731 --> 00:54:04,901
Did the bank give us this certificate?

830
00:54:05,271 --> 00:54:06,830
- Here you go. - You can't send it like this.

831
00:54:06,831 --> 00:54:09,271
Request it again after you include the financial statement.

832
00:54:09,302 --> 00:54:10,572
Yes, sir.

833
00:54:15,541 --> 00:54:17,412
(Data, Get external data)

834
00:54:23,351 --> 00:54:25,190
This is about whether you can prove...

835
00:54:25,191 --> 00:54:27,420
that you can pull your own weight...

836
00:54:27,421 --> 00:54:29,021
as a team member.

837
00:54:30,122 --> 00:54:31,362
Prove it?

838
00:54:44,401 --> 00:54:46,271
I wasn't trapped.

839
00:54:48,782 --> 00:54:50,711
I was just sitting still.

840
00:55:23,081 --> 00:55:24,242
(Shred and recycle)

841
00:55:41,802 --> 00:55:42,831
Teacher.

842
00:55:43,862 --> 00:55:46,271
If it's okay with you, would you like me to copy those for you?

843
00:55:47,231 --> 00:55:48,940
There's quite a lot.

844
00:55:48,941 --> 00:55:49,941
It's fine.

845
00:55:52,612 --> 00:55:54,211
- Thank you. - Of course.

846
00:55:59,481 --> 00:56:02,051
Are you not done copying the Iron Project material?

847
00:56:02,052 --> 00:56:03,322
I'm almost done.

848
00:56:04,452 --> 00:56:07,021
- Bring them to the meeting room. - All right.

849
00:56:27,671 --> 00:56:31,751
Excuse me. This time, can you send an email instead of making copies?

850
00:56:32,182 --> 00:56:33,851
Yes, I can.

851
00:56:40,552 --> 00:56:41,722
Hey, so...

852
00:56:42,461 --> 00:56:45,630
I need to receive a fax, write comments on it,

853
00:56:45,631 --> 00:56:47,231
and send it to another team.

854
00:56:48,061 --> 00:56:49,731
Could you receive the fax for me?

855
00:56:50,061 --> 00:56:51,101
Of course.

856
00:56:51,162 --> 00:56:54,131
But it's coming from the UK. Because of the time difference,

857
00:56:54,642 --> 00:56:56,441
it won't get here until early morning.

858
00:56:57,202 --> 00:56:58,872
Yes, sir. I understand.

859
00:56:59,311 --> 00:57:00,612
Will you really be okay?

860
00:57:03,342 --> 00:57:06,451
What comment should I write on it once I receive the fax?

861
00:57:06,452 --> 00:57:08,322
I'll organize that and send it to you.

862
00:57:08,581 --> 00:57:09,682
Yes, sir.

863
00:57:22,362 --> 00:57:23,862
Who's setting up the meeting room?

864
00:57:24,061 --> 00:57:25,731
Pushover Jang is doing it now.

865
00:57:25,932 --> 00:57:28,471
Then at 3pm, my team will borrow him.

866
00:57:28,472 --> 00:57:31,000
You have to be sure to send him back by 4pm.

867
00:57:31,001 --> 00:57:32,311
I need him to go to the bookbinding room.

868
00:57:34,941 --> 00:57:36,142
Pushover Jang?

869
00:57:59,302 --> 00:58:02,171
Is this the best you can do besides get angry?

870
00:58:03,001 --> 00:58:05,441
Do you even know what people are calling you?

871
00:58:07,412 --> 00:58:09,782
Pushover Jang.

872
00:58:12,412 --> 00:58:14,282
I think that's what they're calling me.

873
00:58:14,782 --> 00:58:15,980
How can you be smiling?

874
00:58:15,981 --> 00:58:19,021
I'm no longer invisible, at least.

875
00:58:20,092 --> 00:58:23,262
Even if I'm a pushover, I'm someone they can see.

876
00:58:27,392 --> 00:58:30,231
I've been looking for you. What are you doing there?

877
00:58:31,901 --> 00:58:32,972
What's this?

878
00:58:35,142 --> 00:58:36,171
Sorry, sir.

879
00:58:41,481 --> 00:58:44,041
I'm someone people even look for when I'm not around.

880
00:58:45,251 --> 00:58:47,081
Compared to being invisible,

881
00:58:47,751 --> 00:58:49,452
it's huge progress.

882
00:58:50,122 --> 00:58:52,822
Why are you trying so hard to stay here?

883
00:58:53,521 --> 00:58:55,262
It doesn't have to be this place necessarily.

884
00:58:55,392 --> 00:58:57,662
- If you go somewhere else... - It has to be this place.

885
00:58:58,691 --> 00:58:59,862
So why is that?

886
00:59:00,592 --> 00:59:04,262
I want to become the nucleus of Taeil Accounting.

887
00:59:04,872 --> 00:59:05,901
Nucleus?

888
00:59:06,802 --> 00:59:08,871
Do you mean something like the core manpower or something?

889
00:59:08,872 --> 00:59:10,941
Oh, core manpower.

890
00:59:12,012 --> 00:59:13,512
That should come first, I guess.

891
00:59:14,572 --> 00:59:15,612
What are you saying?

892
00:59:17,012 --> 00:59:18,782
Then let me ask you one thing too.

893
00:59:20,282 --> 00:59:21,381
Last time,

894
00:59:23,282 --> 00:59:24,952
why did you do that to me?

895
00:59:28,162 --> 00:59:29,561
What do you mean by last time?

896
00:59:31,222 --> 00:59:32,461
On the rooftop.

897
00:59:34,032 --> 00:59:36,202
Why did you teach me...

898
00:59:36,702 --> 00:59:38,131
what I was doing wrong?

899
00:59:38,532 --> 00:59:39,971
Even if you taught me something,

900
00:59:39,972 --> 00:59:42,072
it wouldn't be for my own sake.

901
00:59:42,742 --> 00:59:44,771
You said it was for the benefit of the person who taught me.

902
00:59:45,412 --> 00:59:47,311
What benefit did you get out of it?

903
00:59:48,581 --> 00:59:51,581
What do you, Accountant Han Seung Jo,

904
00:59:53,351 --> 00:59:54,751
get out of teaching me?

905
01:00:16,771 --> 01:00:18,872
You go to the rooftop every chance you get.

906
01:00:20,211 --> 01:00:22,311
You seem to be so comfortable at work.

907
01:00:23,742 --> 01:00:26,182
No way. I'm in the same building as you.

908
01:00:27,811 --> 01:00:29,981
Do you think people are considerate of you...

909
01:00:31,381 --> 01:00:32,992
because you did well?

910
01:00:34,092 --> 01:00:36,691
They're not being considerate. It's more like they're excluding me.

911
01:00:37,061 --> 01:00:39,862
And I know that's all thanks to you, Dad.

912
01:00:40,592 --> 01:00:43,001
And once you take the Chairman's office as you wish,

913
01:00:43,432 --> 01:00:44,731
it'll only get worse.

914
01:00:46,472 --> 01:00:47,601
So?

915
01:00:48,572 --> 01:00:50,302
Did you feel so lonely at work...

916
01:00:50,671 --> 01:00:53,412
that you hired an accountant with only a high school diploma?

917
01:00:54,941 --> 01:00:56,981
Where would you use such a thing?

918
01:00:57,581 --> 01:01:00,581
How dare he come here with nothing but a high school diploma?

919
01:01:01,622 --> 01:01:04,182
The punk who dared to apply here...

920
01:01:04,351 --> 01:01:06,251
and the punk who went ahead and hired him...

921
01:01:07,592 --> 01:01:11,322
That thing will be fired soon, and that's final.

922
01:01:14,791 --> 01:01:17,901
You might end up getting caught and showing your true colors.

923
01:01:19,401 --> 01:01:22,540
People can't even imagine what you're capable of doing...

924
01:01:22,541 --> 01:01:24,142
out of greed.

925
01:01:25,041 --> 01:01:26,472
But isn't it so fascinating?

926
01:01:27,012 --> 01:01:30,282
They don't even know that you're two-faced.

927
01:01:30,881 --> 01:01:33,081
And yet, they call you the Joker.

928
01:01:40,191 --> 01:01:42,461
- Han Seung Jo. - So you should watch out.

929
01:01:43,061 --> 01:01:46,092
It's not even enough that you used your son as a chess piece.

930
01:01:46,532 --> 01:01:50,662
You even gave up being human to get to where you are now.

931
01:01:52,072 --> 01:01:54,302
I could ruin everything for you.

932
01:02:02,412 --> 01:02:06,581
Don't touch anyone from now on.

933
01:02:32,112 --> 01:02:33,311
Jang Ho Woo.

934
01:02:33,512 --> 01:02:37,041
Let me answer the question you asked me earlier.

935
01:02:38,851 --> 01:02:40,081
What do I get out of it?

936
01:02:41,251 --> 01:02:42,481
A wild card.

937
01:02:43,182 --> 01:02:46,492
A card that's nothing but can also become anything at the same time.

938
01:02:47,092 --> 01:02:50,592
No one can predict what it is, so even in an obvious fight,

939
01:02:50,862 --> 01:02:52,961
you can use this card to shake up the whole game.

940
01:02:53,961 --> 01:02:57,001
Like a joker in a stack of playing cards?

941
01:02:57,131 --> 01:02:59,371
I can't tell what you have on the inside from looking at you.

942
01:02:59,372 --> 01:03:01,072
You're just like a joker too.

943
01:03:02,271 --> 01:03:06,012
Figures. There are two jokers in a stack of cards.

944
01:03:10,012 --> 01:03:11,952
So, Jang Ho Woo...

945
01:03:13,581 --> 01:03:15,052
You should join my team.

946
01:03:51,182 --> 01:03:52,591
(Numbers)

947
01:03:52,592 --> 01:03:53,621
Without an inquiry letter,

948
01:03:53,622 --> 01:03:55,690
the audit report and everything will be ruined!

949
01:03:55,691 --> 01:03:56,892
I'll do it.

950
01:03:57,122 --> 01:03:59,560
Do you think Jang Ho Woo will be able to get the inquiry letter?

951
01:03:59,561 --> 01:04:01,362
We won't get it even if an accountant's grandpa goes himself.

952
01:04:02,001 --> 01:04:03,001
Oh, my gosh!

953
01:04:03,002 --> 01:04:04,900
Didn't you hear me say to take a number and wait?

954
01:04:04,901 --> 01:04:06,730
How dare you try to cut in line?

955
01:04:06,731 --> 01:04:09,841
I'm not some strange guy. I'm an accountant.

956
01:04:09,842 --> 01:04:11,241
Let's plant a guy.

957
01:04:11,242 --> 01:04:14,170
Think of it like installing a security camera.

958
01:04:14,171 --> 01:04:16,210
You want to work under Sim Hyung Woo?

959
01:04:16,211 --> 01:04:18,480
Unless you want to get in trouble, get out of there right now.

960
01:04:18,481 --> 01:04:20,850
If that happens, 41 million dollars isn't the issue.

961
01:04:20,851 --> 01:04:22,020
The stock prices will go through the roof.

962
01:04:22,021 --> 01:04:23,051
What happened?

963
01:04:23,052 --> 01:04:25,190
There weren't any particular issues within the audit team.

964
01:04:25,191 --> 01:04:26,191
Did you just turn me down...

965
01:04:26,192 --> 01:04:28,150
when you can't even tell apart friends from enemies?

966
01:04:28,151 --> 01:04:30,262
It seems like friends and enemies aren't decided by people...

967
01:04:31,222 --> 01:04:32,992
but by timing.